The paper deals with scheduling wireless links in a network, which is a topic related to computer networks and communication systems. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category. The paper also involves the computation of a novel edge-chromatic indicator, which is related to graph theory and optimization, suggesting cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as possible categories. The paper also mentions the use of linear programming to solve the optimization problem, which is related to mathematical optimization and operations research, suggesting cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) as another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the possibility of increasing network capacity by using fractional edge coloring, which is related to graph theory and combinatorics, suggesting cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as a possible category.
